I read the article and comments. Holy sh*t.

The world has recycled itself no matter what era you take into consideration.

Especially, considering the generation of hypersensitivity many in our current time experience.

To assume that ancient civilizations were “cases of civilization and its deconditions” ignoring their superiority in “sustainability and well-being,” because they didn’t move forward is just plain dramatic.

The article itself proposes nothing. Only pointing out how our society ignores great strides in sustainability which were established in prior times.

Sure, today we have our convenience with cell phones, televisions, artificial waves that “enlighten our minds with magic.” However, Fox News has a lot to do with narcissism and mindless haughtiness, not the microwave.

Our society has turned the impeccable and nonsensical. There is no middle ground. It is either bitter or sweet. Not only that, but the convenience packages most everything so that it becomes our burden not to mention another insult.

Even established societies had difficulties to please their populous. For example, the democracy once experienced in the Roman Empire was only introduced when it was noticed that not the entire populace was striving for the same goals.
